ructure**\\n\\nI’m considering the need for metadata in native images for test classes and agent records. The guideline about not using `$` in names suggests it's for inner classes, but I wonder about nested classes. It might be safer to create separate top-level fixture classes while maintaining a one-to-one mapping between report classes and generated test files. Helper classes could fit in, too. Also, ensuring class and file naming conventions are handled correctly is important for organization.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class metadata requirements**\\n\\nI'm pondering if the argument string from `Class.getName().replace` should be a constant. Inside the library, it’s more dynamic, and I wonder if the native image might include test classes since they can be referenced with class literals in constants. Using class literals can help with naming and assertions, making classes reachable. Even without metadata, `Class.forName` may still require reflection metadata for a native image. Tracking this seems essential.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_AvjKksiwTVkiBaryVKl6ZTGR|fc_07083aa4e0d3106d0169ef6f7ba8a8819689e67434d8ea391c", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/src/test/java/asm/asm/ClassWriterTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.LinkedList;\n", "newText": "import java.util.AbstractList;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.LinkedList;\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS_NAME = \"asm/asm/generated/MergedCollections\";\n    private static final String ARRAY_LIST_NAME = ArrayList.class.getName().replace('.', '/');\n    private static final String LINKED_LIST_NAME = LinkedList.class.getName().replace('.', '/');\n    private static final String ABSTRACT_LIST_NAME = \"java/util/AbstractList\";\n", "newText": "    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS_NAME = \"asm/asm/ClassWriterGeneratedMergedLists\";\n    private static f